Make big data uncomplicated and easy for everyone to see information in new and amazing ways through interactive visualisations created in Power View and Power Map.  For example mapping population flow through a city is difficult to interpret using traditional spread sheets and tables, however, the use of visualisation brings the data to life and inspires thought.

The emergence of 3rd party apps, utilising government data and created by the private sector, provide a competitive landscape that drives wider adoption tactics such as socialising, improved applications at no cost and with more value through features.

Open data initiatives supported by Microsoft Azure creates an ecosystem of 3rd party commercial providers who consume the data to produce services and insights valuable to both the public sector and citizens alike.  This results in service improvements that are not funded by public sector budget.
